<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">CHICKEN-BROCCOLI STIR-FRY</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page059.article002.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY KAMIN WILLIAMS</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 4 to 6 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 cup uncooked long-grain white rice </p><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons vegetable oil </p><p class="no-indent">1½ pounds boneless skinless chicken breast, thinly sliced </p><p class="no-indent">1½ cups sliced celery </p><p class="no-indent">1½ cups broccoli florets </p><p class="no-indent">1 cup sliced carrot </p><p class="no-indent">1 cup chopped onion </p><p class="no-indent">2 cups chicken broth </p><p class="no-indent">3 tablespoons soy sauce </p><p class="no-indent">¼ cup cold water</p><p class="no-indent"> 2 tablespoons cornstarch </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Prepare rice according to package directions and keep warm. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken, and cook, stirring frequently, for 4 minutes. Add celery and next 3 ingredients. Cook, stirring frequently, for 4 minutes. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. Stir in broth and soy sauce; bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer for 2 minutes. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">4. In a small bowl, stir together ¼ cup cold water and cornstarch. Stir into chicken mixture, and cook for 1 minute, or until sauce is thickened. Serve over warm rice.</p></div>
